Chromatic dragons are of an evil alignment.
Evil dragons receive a STR and DEX bonus, and an INT and WIS penalty. 
They gain an advantage in melee combat to make up for their weaker damage
from SP.
Black dragons have a damage type of acid.
Red dragons have a damage type of fire.
White dragons have a damage type of cold.
Blue dragons have a damage type of lightning.
Green dragons have a damage type of disease.

Gem dragons are of a neutral alignment.
Neutral dragons do not get any stat bonuses or penalties. They gain a much
higher HP and SP regen however. They have the advantage of being able to pick
melee or sp damage as their main choice.
Crystal dragons have a damage type of light.
Topaz dragons have a damage type of cold.
Amethyst dragons have a damage type of poison.
Emerald dragons have a damage type of disease.
Sapphire dragons have a damage type of sound.

Metal dragons are of a good alignment.
Good dragons receive a STR and DEX penalty, and an INT and WIS bonus.
They gain an advantage in damage from SP to make up for their weaker damage
from combat.
Brass dragons have a damage type of disease.
Copper dragons have a damage type of acid.
Bronze dragons have a damage type of lightning.
Silver dragons have a damage type of cold.
Gold dragons have a damage type of fire.

Except for transforming, you will need to stay in your declared alignment  
to perform your Dragon abilities.
